java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.trofimov.implementor.Implementor

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      The main function for Implementor.

      If the first argument is "-jar" calls implementJar(Class, Path), otherwise calls implement(Class, Path). Last two arguments define token and path.

      If any argument is null or number of arguments doesn't equal to 3 in case of "-jar" and 2 in other case, then generates ImplerException error.

      Parameters:
      args - given arguments

    • canImplement

      private boolean canImplement(Class<?> token)
      Checks if it's possible to create implementation of a class or interface. It's not possible to generate implementation of primitives, Enum, private or final tokens and of interfaces, which constructors are all private.
      Parameters:
      token - specified class/interface
      Returns:
      true if it's possible to create a class, which implements token, false otherwise
